1. The method returns a string representation of the largest number formed by arranging the elements in the input array `nums`.
2. The returned string is not null.
3. The length of the returned string is equal to the length of the input array `nums`.
4. The returned string consists of the same digits as the input array `nums`, but arranged in a way that forms the largest number.
5. The returned string does not contain any leading zeros, except when the input array `nums` contains only zeros.
